Global Lake Database, version 2 (GLDBv2).
Lake-Depth Data Set, fresh-water lakes.
April 2014. 

The data set is developed by Ekatherina Kourzeneva, kourzeneva_at_rshu.ru
                             Margarita Choulga, botan4ik_at_hotmail.com 
(using a prototype data set of Natalia Schneider, natalia.schneider_at_web.de).

The present "Fresh-Water Lake-Depth Data Set" file contains information about a number of world fresh-water lakes.
Each lake is identified with its location (geographical co-ordinates) and its international name. 
Whenever available, the local name used in the country where the lake is located, 
the lake mean depth, its maximum depth, and its surface area are given. 
The lakes in the lists are ordered with respect to the continent and the country of their location. 
The continents and the countries are ordered alphabetically. 

The following sources of data are used. 
Notice that the "mailto" tags do not contain valid email addresses. 
The "@" is replaced with "_at_". 
Please correct manually in the address field of your mail program.

Switzerland:
    data from Swiss Federal Office for Water and Geology, www.bwg.admin.ch/service/hydro/e/indiv.htm
              daniel.streit_at_bwg.admin.ch, Daniel Streit
    NB: names of the lakes are mainly national (sometimes without international one)
        there are co-ordinates of hydrological stations on the shore of the lake
        co-ordinates are converted from Swiss National co-ordinate
        mean depth is estimated from total water volume and surface area or (max depth)/2
